(AUTOPOV APPLICATION FLOW \(END-TO-END\)) Tj
T*
T*
T*
(This document explains how AutoPoV works from start to finish, based on the current code) Tj
T*
(paths.) Tj
T*
T*
(1. SCAN IS STARTED) Tj
T*
T*
(A scan can be triggered in three ways:) Tj
T*
(- **Git repo** \(`/api/scan/git`\)) Tj
T*
(- **ZIP upload** \(`/api/scan/zip`\)) Tj
T*
(- **Paste code** \(`/api/scan/paste`\)) Tj
T*
T*
(The backend creates a scan record with a new `scan_id` and initializes status + logs.) Tj
T*
T*
(2. SOURCE PREPARATION) Tj
T*
T*
(- **Git**: repository is cloned into a scan workspace.) Tj
T*
(- **ZIP**: archive is extracted into a scan workspace.) Tj
T*
(- **Paste**: code is saved to a file in a scan workspace.) Tj
T*
T*
(The scan record is updated with `codebase_path`.) Tj
T*
T*
(3. INGESTION) Tj
T*
T*
(The codebase is chunked and indexed for analysis \(vector store\). Logs record file counts) Tj
T*
(and chunk counts.) Tj
T*
T*
(4. DISCOVERY \(CANDIDATE FINDINGS\)) Tj
T*
T*
(AutoPoV finds candidate issues by combining:) Tj
T*
(- **CodeQL** \(if available\)) Tj
T*
(- **Heuristic scout** \(rule-based patterns\)) Tj
T*
(- **LLM scout** \(optional LLM analysis\)) Tj
T*
T*
(Candidates are merged and deduplicated.) Tj
T*
T*
(5. INVESTIGATION \(LLM VALIDATION\)) Tj
T*
T*
(Each candidate is analyzed by a routed model:) Tj
T*
(- Verdict: `REAL` or `FALSE_POSITIVE`) Tj
T*
(- Confidence score) Tj
T*
(- Explanation + vulnerable snippet) Tj
T*
(- Cost + model used) Tj
T*
T*
(Only `REAL` findings continue to PoV generation.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
3 0 obj
<< /Length 1564 >>
stream
BT
/F1 12 Tf
72 720 Td
14 TL
T*
(6. POV GENERATION) Tj
T*
T*
(A PoV script is generated for confirmed findings:) Tj
T*
(- Uses the routed model \(OpenRouter auto by default\)) Tj
T*
(- Script must print **`VULNERABILITY TRIGGERED`** when successful) Tj
T*
(- Script is designed to execute directly against the vulnerable code context) Tj
T*
T*
(7. POV VALIDATION) Tj
T*
T*
(AutoPoV validates PoVs using a hybrid flow:) Tj
T*
(- **Static validation** \(fast\)) Tj
T*
(- **Unit-test execution** \(isolated harness\)) Tj
T*
(- **LLM validation** \(fallback\)) Tj
T*
T*
(If PoV does not conclusively validate, it proceeds to Docker execution.) Tj
T*
T*
(8. POV EXECUTION \(PROOF STEP\)) Tj
T*
T*
(PoVs are run in an isolated Docker container:) Tj
T*
(- If output contains **`VULNERABILITY TRIGGERED`**, the vulnerability is proven.) Tj
T*
(- Results \(stdout/stderr, exit code\) are stored.) Tj
T*
T*
(9. RESULTS + REPORTS SAVED) Tj
T*
T*
(Results are saved to:) Tj
T*
(- `results/runs/<scan_id>.json`) Tj
T*
(- `results/<scan_id>_report.json`) Tj
T*
(- `results/<scan_id>_report.pdf`) Tj
T*
T*
(PoV scripts are saved to:) Tj
T*
(- `results/povs/` \(only for confirmed findings\)) Tj
T*
T*
(10. UI RESULTS) Tj
T*
T*
(The UI displays:) Tj
T*
(- Summary metrics \(total, confirmed, cost, PoV success\)) Tj
T*
(- Per-finding details \(explanation, vulnerable code, PoV status\)) Tj
T*
(- Validation method and PoV execution output) Tj
T*
(- Reports \(JSON + PDF\)) Tj
T*
T*
(---) Tj
T*
T*
(KEY API ENDPOINTS) Tj
T*
T*
(- Start scan \(Git\): `POST /api/scan/git`) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
